評量配分比重

"For students who are taking the seminar course for credit:
I.	Each student will be in charge of hosting invited speakers once. The seminar host’s responsibility include:
A.	Communicating with invited speakers about:
1.	Obtaining the lecture topic, abstract, and CV of speakers
2.	Confirming their itinerary to location (NYMU or NCU)
3.	Reminding speakers to bring their post office account
4.	Reminding speakers that lectures will be in English
B.	Hosting the speaker and assisting them to setup their presentation
C.	Introducing the speakers and chair the Q&A session

II.	The basic score is 75 points for each student.
III.	 Each student is required to ask at least three questions per semester. Each question is worth three points. The TA will take note on who ask what in each seminar session.
A.	Notice: state your name first, and then ask your question(s)
IV.	 If your performance of hosting your speaker is good, you will get five points.
V.	You will get an extra 0~5 points (according to your performance) from your introduction of the speakers."
